------------------
ChucK-DMX VERSIONS log
------------------

0.1.1 (February 2026)
=======
(fixed) critical thread safety: data races on protocol, universe,
    update interval, and last send time in all send paths; all shared
    state is now snapshotted under a single lock before transmission
(fixed) potential deadlock from inconsistent lock ordering between
    serial_mutex and state_mutex
(fixed) exception slicing (throw e instead of throw) in all ChucK VM
    callbacks; exceptions no longer propagate through the ChucK VM
(fixed) deinit called on uninitialized protocols (sACN Deinit without
    Init, artnet_destroy on nullptr); initialization state is now
    tracked with per-protocol flags
(fixed) Windows usleep macro resolving to Sleep(0) for sub-millisecond
    DMX break timing; replaced with QueryPerformanceCounter busy-wait
(fixed) sACN Init/Deinit not reference-counted across multiple DMX
    instances; added global reference counting
(fixed) reconnect attempts on every failed send flooding stderr; added
    5-second backoff cooldown between reconnect attempts
(added) background send thread via start()/stop() for automatic DMX
    transmission at the configured rate
(added) fade(channel, target, durationMs) for linear channel transitions
    processed by the background thread; setting a channel directly
    cancels any active fade on that channel
(added) channels(startChannel, values[]) for atomic batch updates of
    consecutive DMX channels under a single lock
(added) channel getter: channel(ch) with one argument returns the
    current value (0-255) of a DMX channel
(added) connected() method returning whether the current protocol is
    initialized and ready to send
(added) DMX.ports() static method to enumerate available serial ports
    as a comma-separated string
(added) sACN priority support via priority(p) getter/setter (0-200,
    default 100); can be changed live after init via ChangePriority
(added) blackout() method to zero all 512 channels and cancel all
    active fades across all universes
(added) static protocol constants: DMX.SERIAL_RAW, DMX.SERIAL,
    DMX.SACN, DMX.ARTNET
(added) multi-universe support: addUniverse(uni) and removeUniverse(uni)
    for managing multiple DMX universes per instance; sACN adds/removes
    universes live, ArtNet supports up to 4 ports per node
(added) universe() setter auto-creates universe data if it doesn't
    exist; universe selects the active universe for channel/fade ops
(added) name(string) getter/setter for sACN source name and ArtNet
    short/long name (default: 'ChucK DMX'); sACN updates live via
    ChangeName, ArtNet requires re-init
(updated) init() now returns int (1 on success, 0 on failure) so
    ChucK scripts can detect and handle initialization errors
(updated) channel values are now clamped to 0-255 with a warning
    instead of silent truncation via unsigned char cast
(updated) protocol/rate/port/universe setters now return their value
    for idiomatic ChucK chaining (e.g., DMX.SACN => dmx.protocol)
(updated) universe setter validates range 1-63999; auto-creates
    universe data buffer on first use
(updated) send() transmits all configured universes for sACN/ArtNet;
    Serial sends only the active universe
(updated) priority() live update now applies to all configured sACN
    universes
(updated) all error handling uses stderr warnings instead of throwing
    C++ exceptions through the ChucK VM
(updated) Enttec protocol magic numbers replaced with named constants
(updated) CMakeLists.txt: removed undefined ${SERIAL_LIBRARY} and
    ${ARTNET_LIBRARY} variables from target_link_libraries
(updated) DMX-test.ck to demonstrate new API features

